Dear Ian,

 	Last month I decided to open source tth in its entirety. It is now on
source forge, including the flex source. sourceforge.net/projects/tth/

I propose that the Debian package should now depend upon that sourceforge
distribution. It contains a free license, which I mildly prefer to the MIT
license. If there's a strong reason that Debian objects to the license for tth
on sourceforge, please let me know and I'll consider what to do.

Also, I am abandoning the distinction between tth and tthgold, so no reduced
functionality package is included now.

 	Ian Hutchinson
 	http://www.psfc.mit.edu/people/hutch/


